    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Multi-panelled sanctuary screens like those used in the Eastern Orthodox church, but on a small scale. Used in private devotion in a family chapel, in private homes, or for travel. The depiction of saints matched that of the church iconostasis.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046892/Grove Art Online (2003-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047407/McKenzie, Windows to Heaven (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047408/Milwaukee Art Museum (2004-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Voor sanctuaria bestemde schermen bestaande uit meerdere panelen zoals die in oosters-orthodoxe kerken voorkomen, maar dan op kleinere schaal uitgevoerd. Gebruikt voor privédevotie in familiekapellen, woonhuizen of op reis. De heiligen werden op dezelfde wijze afgebeeld als op iconostasen in kerken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由多片壁板製成的較小型聖所圍屏，形似東正教教堂中使用的圍屏，用於家族小禮拜堂、住宅或旅途中舉行的私人敬拜儀式。可攜式聖像屏上的聖徒像和教堂聖像屏所繪相同。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wand mit mehreren Tafeln wie solche die in der orthodoxen Kirche verwendet werden, aber in einem kleineren Maßstab. Sie wurde für die private Andacht in einer Familienkapelle in Privathäusern oder auf Reisen verwendet. Die Heiligendarstellungen entsprechen denen der kirchlichen Ikonastase.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
